race.comment: BRERETON (10) missed the kick and any chance of winning when fresh from a spell in the $1 million Syndicate over 1100m at the Gold Coast last start. Has a better second-up record. Beautifully drawn so if he jumps okay a big run looks on the cards. FLEETWOOD (3) won an open sprint over 1100m at the Gold Coast three runs back but his since struggled in a couple of 1200m races. Gets in nicely after Williams' claim so give him one more chance. TIGER TIE (12) started at a very short quote and led all the way for an effortless first-up win over this journey at Ballina recently. Tougher assignment today and he has missed at two previous second-up runs, but conditions today look right. WONDEREACH (9) was brave in defeat over 1100m at Rosehill a fortnight ago. Distance specialist who should be about the mark again. VODKA MARTINI (1) is back in grade on recent runs and is a two-time winner here at this distance.
